      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 1909: loadMissingBodyOverwrites treats the absence of bodyOverwrite as the only \u0027not processed\u0027 state. If a plugin returns an empty overwrite, the message remains missing the key and will be reprocessed on every load/reload path, which can repeatedly invoke expensive plugin work for messages that intentionally have no overwrite. Cache a processed empty state or a separate marker so negative results are not recomputed indefinitely.\n```suggestion\nif (boIt \u003d\u003d single[0].pluginData.end() || boIt-\u003esecond.empty()) {\n    std::lock_guard const lk(loadedHistory_.mutex);\n    if (auto it \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(id); it !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end())\n        it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d \"\";\n    continue;\n}\n```",
