      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2258: SwarmLoaded is emitted before body overwrite transforms are applied, so clients receive the loaded batch without plugin-provided bodyOverwrite data and only later get per-message update signals. This contradicts the new ChatHandler API contract that transforms happen before SwarmLoaded and can cause visible flicker or stale initial render. Apply the transform/reload before emitting, or integrate transformSwarmMessages into loadMessages result construction. Suggested shape:\n```suggestion\n#ifdef ENABLE_PLUGIN\nif (auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock())\n    convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\n#endif\nemitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n```",
      "revId": "1f6ef9906c51f4c7d65d8716430c56bddf331841",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
