      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 293: transformSwarmMessages holds ChatServicesManager::mtx_ while executing plugin handler code. Plugin transform implementations can invoke services such as updateMessageBodyOverwrite/reloadBodyOverwriteConversations, which call back into ChatServicesManager and acquire the same mutex, creating the deadlock pattern that this patch avoids elsewhere. Collect eligible handlers under the lock, then invoke transformSwarmMessages outside it.\n```suggestion\nstd::vector\u003cChatHandler*\u003e handlers;\n{\n    std::lock_guard lk(mtx_);\n    // collect eligible handlers\n}\nfor (auto* handler : handlers)\n    handler-\u003etransformSwarmMessages(messages, accountId, conversationId);\n```",
