      "message": "[Critical] Line 520: Raw ChatHandler pointers are collected under mtx_ and then used after the lock is released. If a plugin is unloaded concurrently, unregisterChatHandler can erase/destroy the handler before notifyChatSubject, detach, or setPreferenceAttribute runs, leading to use-after-free. Keep the handler alive across the unlocked call, e.g. collect shared ownership if ChatHandlerPtr is shared_ptr, or otherwise add a lifetime guard around plugin unload and these callbacks.\n```suggestion\nstd::vector\u003cChatHandlerPtr\u003e toNotify;\n{\n    std::lock_guard lk(mtx_);\n    for (auto\u0026 chatHandler : chatHandlers_) {\n        if (chatHandler-\u003eid().find(rootPath) !\u003d std::string::npos \u0026\u0026 chatHandler-\u003epreferenceMapHasKey(key))\n            toNotify.push_back(chatHandler);\n    }\n}\nfor (auto\u0026 handler : toNotify)\n    handler-\u003esetPreferenceAttribute(key, value);\n```",
